I think some days, you just want
the chocolate fudge brownie.

00:32:05.560 --> 00:32:07.090
Eat the chocolate fudge brownie.

00:32:07.090 --> 00:32:09.040
Eat it.

00:32:09.040 --> 00:32:11.840
And I find what happens
is, what we'll often do--

00:32:11.840 --> 00:32:13.120
sometimes there's just--

00:32:13.120 --> 00:32:14.110
we want that thing.

00:32:14.110 --> 00:32:16.000
And that's OK.

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.990
It's OK to have that, and to
eat it, and feel good about it.

00:32:19.990 --> 00:32:22.540
When you eat something
that your body--

00:32:22.540 --> 00:32:25.210
let's just say, for
example, you really

00:32:25.210 --> 00:32:28.360
want this chocolate
fudge brownie.

00:32:28.360 --> 00:32:29.619
That's what your craving is.

00:32:29.619 --> 00:32:31.660
And you're like, oh-- but
you're beating yourself

00:32:31.660 --> 00:32:32.200
up in your head.

00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.380
You're like, well, I
shouldn't have that.

00:32:33.380 --> 00:32:34.250
I don't want that.

00:32:34.250 --> 00:32:36.340
I shouldn't do it.

00:32:36.340 --> 00:32:38.455
And then you're like, well,
maybe I'll just have--

00:32:38.455 --> 00:32:40.780
then the chocolate fudge
brownies are right there.

00:32:40.780 --> 00:32:43.139
And you're like, oh,
I'll just have one bite.

00:32:43.139 --> 00:32:44.180
And then you're like, no.

00:32:44.180 --> 00:32:46.346
And then your friends are
over eating carrot sticks.

00:32:46.346 --> 00:32:48.280
You're like, why
can't I be like them?

00:32:48.280 --> 00:32:51.460
And then it's like this whole
stressful thing in your mind.

00:32:51.460 --> 00:32:53.200
And what you're doing
to your body, when

00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.420
you stress about eating
something like that,

00:32:55.420 --> 00:32:59.740
is physically, that stress
is no different than any type

00:32:59.740 --> 00:33:02.080
of other stress, like if
someone's attacking you.

00:33:02.080 --> 00:33:04.640
Your blood rushes
to your feet to run,

00:33:04.640 --> 00:33:06.316
to your hands to
fight something off,

00:33:06.316 --> 00:33:07.440
and to your brain to think.

00:33:07.440 --> 00:33:08.920
So the last thing it's
thinking about doing

00:33:08.920 --> 00:33:10.378
is digesting that
chocolate brownie

00:33:10.378 --> 00:33:11.800
that you're stressing about.

00:33:11.800 --> 00:33:13.390
So if you really
want something--

00:33:13.390 --> 00:33:15.224
or then the other thing
we do is we're like,

00:33:15.224 --> 00:33:16.931
wow, I really want
the chocolate brownie,

00:33:16.931 --> 00:33:18.340
but I'm trying to be healthy.

00:33:18.340 --> 00:33:24.070
So I'm going to have
some cacao nibs,

00:33:24.070 --> 00:33:25.450
and then you eat the cacao nibs.

00:33:25.450 --> 00:33:27.360
And you're like, but
that doesn't satisfy it.

00:33:27.360 --> 00:33:29.836
And then you have
something kind of bitter,

00:33:29.836 --> 00:33:31.210
so then you want
something sweet.

00:33:31.210 --> 00:33:34.510
So then you're like,
well, now I'll have fruit.

00:33:34.510 --> 00:33:36.470
Now I want something salty.

00:33:36.470 --> 00:33:40.915
And then you spend all
day trying to get the--

00:33:40.915 --> 00:33:43.570
when if you would have just
ate the chocolate brownie

00:33:43.570 --> 00:33:46.750
and appreciated it, and
savored it, and looked at it

00:33:46.750 --> 00:33:49.250
as something like--

00:33:49.250 --> 00:33:51.970
I guess precious-- looked
something at it like, wow,

00:33:51.970 --> 00:33:54.129
this is something I really
get to enjoy right now.

00:33:54.129 --> 00:33:56.420
I'm going to savor it, I'm
going to feel good about it,

00:33:56.420 --> 00:33:58.630
I'm going to eat it with
love, I'm going to--

00:33:58.630 --> 00:34:00.670
really just bring
that into that.

00:34:00.670 --> 00:34:02.520
And then you'll end
up processing it.

00:34:02.520 --> 00:34:05.020
You'll get any nutrients that
are in that chocolate brownie.

00:34:05.020 --> 00:34:06.560
You will get them.

00:34:06.560 --> 00:34:08.659
And you'll also
digest it differently.

